OL,3,CGovernment's Rwanda bill suffers
OL,4,Cdefeats in Lords
OL,6,FThe government suffered its third
OL,7,Fdefeat of the day in the House of
OL,8,FLords when peers voted by 277 votes to
OL,9,F167, majority 110, in favour of
OL,10,Festablishing a monitoring mechanism
OL,11,Fable to determine whether the
OL,12,Fsafeguards in the UK-Rwanda Treaty
OL,13,Fhave been, and continue to be, fully
OL,14,Fimplemented.
