OL,3,CGovernment's Rwanda bill suffers
OL,4,Cdefeats in Lords
OL,6,FIn a further blow to the government, a
OL,7,Fproposed change to the legislation
OL,8,Fthat would allow the presumption that
OL,9,FRwanda is safe to be challenged in the
OL,10,Fcourts was backed by 258 votes to 171,
OL,11,Fmajority 87. A short time later, a
OL,12,Fsimilar consequential amendment also
OL,13,Fwent through by 260 votes to 169,
OL,14,Fmajority 91, bring the total number of
OL,15,Fgovernment defeats to five.
