OL,3,CGovernment's Rwanda bill suffers
OL,4,Cdefeats in Lords
OL,6,FThis heavy government defeat sets the
OL,7,Fstage for an extended tussle between
OL,8,Fthe Commons and Lords during "ping-
OL,9,Fpong", where legislation is batted
OL,10,Fbetween the two Houses until agreement
OL,11,Fis reached.
OL,13,FThe Lords can't block or vote down
OL,14,Flegislation, but it can encourage the
OL,15,Fgovernment to think again, encouraging
OL,16,Fit to compromise where there is
OL,17,Fdisagreement between the two chambers.
